    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nClearing the scrollback leaves a dangling line that appears when leaving insert mode. The line disappears when entering insert mode again.\r\n\r\nThe video shows an example of using `reset` + `set scrollback=0` + `set scrollback=-1`, but just using plain `clear` reproduces the issue (see repro steps below)\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c9e89446-c6e0-444e-ab0c-70e4cef9b83a\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean -u minimal.lua\r\n:term\r\ndmesg # or anything with output greater than number of lines in the window\r\nclear\r\nC-\\ C-N\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo dangling lines should appear when going back to normal mode\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNo, it does not have clear scrollback feature\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.5\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.35.2\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nHomebrew",
